cs.HC, cs.CYBER, cs.OH, cs.SI, cs.NI 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction): The paper proposes a new smartphone-based system for health care, monitoring, and diagnosis, which involves designing an easy-to-use smartphone application for operating the whole system. This falls under the domain of human-computer interaction. 
2. cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy): The proposed system involves the digitization of health monitoring and diagnostic devices, which may raise concerns about cybersecurity and privacy. 
3. cs.OH (Other Computer Science): The paper proposes a new system for public health care, which may not fit into any specific sub-category of computer science. 
4. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): The proposed system may involve the use of social and information networks to disseminate health-related information and connect health workers in rural areas. 
5. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The proposed system may involve the use of networking and internet architecture to connect health workers and transmit health-related data.
